<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1181.109521.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Tetranemertes ocelata sp. nov. A external appearance in life B proboscis armature showing bilobed basis and sculpted stylets C head compressed under coverslip to show number and arrangement of eyes, cerebral organs and cerebral ganglia D head in ventro-lateral view showing eyes and the cephalic furrow (arrowhead). Abbreviations: cg - cerebral ganglion, co - cerebral organ. Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 50 μm (B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/916928" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

